LAST WEEK TONIGHT
WITH JOHN OLIVER

00:27.070 --> 00:28.180
SEASON VI
EPISODE 6

00:28.240 --> 00:31.140
Welcome to Last Week Tonight.

00:31.180 --> 00:34.020
I'm John Oliver,
thank you for joining us.

00:34.040 --> 00:37.240
A quick recap of the week,
a busy one for the administration,

00:38.010 --> 00:41.030
from Trump's attacks
on the Affordable Healthcare Act,

00:41.060 --> 00:45.030
to his threats to close the southern
border, to Bernhardt's hearing.

00:45.050 --> 00:47.220
He is Trump's pick for
Secretary of the Interior

00:47.240 --> 00:50.160
and a former oil lobbyist,
so he's pretty swampy,

00:50.180 --> 00:56.030
which some activists drew attention
to, as you'll see over his shoulder.

00:56.100 --> 00:58.220
I have worked with many of you
and your staff.

00:59.020 --> 01:01.210
I have met with many of you
in person, and by phone,

01:01.860 --> 01:04.010
on various issues that were
of a concern to you

01:04.030 --> 01:07.840
and I will always make myself
available to your requests.

01:08.010 --> 01:11.920
Yeah! Nicely done. That woman
in the mask was there for a while.

01:11.950 --> 01:15.910
Because ten minutes later?
Still there. 20 minutes? Still there!

01:15.980 --> 01:20.060
45 minutes? Still there!
An hour later? Still there!

01:20.900 --> 01:24.930
It is pretty funny, although,
I would not be doing my job

01:24.950 --> 01:27.910
if I didn't point out
that this is a "swamp creature"

01:27.930 --> 01:31.840
and technically what she's wearing
is a "lagoon creature" mask,

01:31.860 --> 01:34.000
and that distinction
might not mean much to you

01:34.020 --> 01:38.060
but in the aquatic goblin communities,
confusing the two is pretty racist.

01:38.860 --> 01:42.080
This week was dominated by
the fallout from the Mueller Report.

01:42.850 --> 01:46.960
William Barr submitted this
summary of its contents to Congress.

01:47.000 --> 01:51.010
The investigation did not establish
that members of the Trump campaign

01:51.050 --> 01:54.030
conspired or coordinated
with Russian government

01:54.050 --> 01:56.910
in its election
interference activities.

01:56.930 --> 01:59.070
When it comes
to the question of obstruction,

01:59.840 --> 02:02.970
Barr said Mueller did not have
enough evidence to prosecute

02:03.380 --> 02:05.530
but could not
exonerate the president.

02:06.390 --> 02:11.420
Report did not establish a conspiracy
between Russia and Trump's campaign,

02:11.440 --> 02:14.370
which is undeniably
good news for the president.

02:14.390 --> 02:17.580
The fact that Mueller did not exonerate
him on obstruction of justice

02:17.600 --> 02:19.430
is pretty remarkable.

02:19.450 --> 02:21.400
It might
prompt headlines like:

02:21.420 --> 02:23.530
"President May Have
Obstructed Justice."

02:24.370 --> 02:25.590
Which is why it's been weird
to see

02:26.360 --> 02:29.550
the good news for the president
often shoving aside the bad.

02:30.410 --> 02:32.560
The O.J. Simpson murders were
not reported as:

02:32.580 --> 02:35.580
"Affordable House
Becomes Available In Brentwood."

02:35.600 --> 02:39.430
There's something pretty big
missing from that headline.

02:39.490 --> 02:41.520
All week, the president's supporters

02:41.540 --> 02:44.460
took their one good news
and rounded it up to two.

02:44.500 --> 02:46.580
No collusion.
No obstruction of justice.

02:46.600 --> 02:48.550
No obstruction, no collusion.

02:48.570 --> 02:52.440
No collusion,
no obstruction, nothing.

02:52.500 --> 02:56.360
Victorious, exonerated,
vindicated.

02:56.430 --> 02:59.420
Trump was not
completely exonerated.

02:59.440 --> 03:03.470
The report literally used the words
"does not exonerate him."

03:03.930 --> 03:08.800
Mueller could have been clearer
is if he put hand clap emojis

03:08.820 --> 03:09.900
between every word.

03:09.990 --> 03:15.000
Normally this is where we would
do a deep dive into the details,

03:15.020 --> 03:18.810
explaining all the possible
implications.

03:18.840 --> 03:20.940
The problem is...
We still haven't seen it.

03:20.970 --> 03:24.040
Congress hasn't seen it.
Even the president hasn't seen it.

03:24.820 --> 03:27.970
We know what Trump's own attorney
general thinks we need to know,

03:27.990 --> 03:31.020
a man who, unsolicited
and before he got his current job,

03:31.040 --> 03:35.030
sent top DOJ officials a memo ruling
out obstruction of justice charges

03:35.800 --> 03:36.900
against the president.

03:36.920 --> 03:39.950
There are plenty of qualifiers
and questions left here,

03:39.970 --> 03:43.020
it's strange to see Trump's
supporters saying this.

03:43.860 --> 03:48.840
One year, 10 months and six days.
$40 million of taxpayer money wasted.

03:48.880 --> 03:49.940
It was all a waste.

03:49.960 --> 03:53.040
How did we ever waste
two years of America on this?

03:53.810 --> 03:56.940
All the Democrats yakking,
billions of hours of hot air

03:56.960 --> 03:58.890
coming out of Democrat mouths.

03:58.910 --> 04:02.800
All they got for it was this t-shirt.
They got nothing out of it.

04:02.820 --> 04:07.890
If there's one authority figure I trust
on free shirts, it's gonna be that man.

04:08.200 --> 04:12.200
There is no way actual U.S. currency
was exchanged for that outfit.

04:12.230 --> 04:15.350
He's dressed like a personal-injury
attorney whose portrait

04:15.370 --> 04:19.240
just got MeToo'ed off the wall
of an airport Palm steakhouse.

04:19.260 --> 04:23.160
DOJ could well take in more
than it spent on the investigation

04:23.180 --> 04:26.390
just in the form of asset forfeitures
from Paul Manafort alone.

04:27.160 --> 04:31.330
As we've said before, even if
the investigation didn't conclude

04:31.350 --> 04:35.320
Trump conspired with the Russians,
doesn't mean it was a waste of time.

04:35.340 --> 04:38.340
It's easy to forget how much
we've already learned,

04:38.360 --> 04:41.400
directly or indirectly, from
Mueller's investigation,

04:42.180 --> 04:44.370
as so much has slowly
trickled out over two years.

04:44.390 --> 04:48.280
Try and imagine
that it all came out at once,

04:48.310 --> 04:50.210
and a single headline said:

04:50.230 --> 04:53.190
"Russia Confirmed
To Have Interfered In Election"

04:53.210 --> 04:57.280
"And President's Campaign Manager,
Multiple Advisers Convicted Of Crimes"

04:57.300 --> 05:01.160
"And Trump And His Team Lied
About Business With Russia,"

05:01.190 --> 05:04.280
"And Trump May Have Committed
Campaign Finance Violations"

05:04.300 --> 05:08.240
"To Cover Up Affair With Adult Film
Star, After His Wife Gave Birth,"

05:08.500 --> 05:11.490
"And Which He Also Attempted
To Continue, But Ended Up"

05:11.510 --> 05:14.650
"Sitting Next To Her In A Hotel Room
And Watching "Shark Week.'"

05:14.670 --> 05:17.490
All of that happened,
and we know it,

05:17.530 --> 05:20.650
as a result
of Mueller's investigation.

05:20.680 --> 05:23.720
This scandal has been sitting
in plain sight for so long,

05:24.490 --> 05:25.640
we've stopped noticing it,

05:25.660 --> 05:28.690
much like a woman in an
increasingly-sweaty fish mask.

05:28.720 --> 05:33.560
The weirdest thing about this
situation is how somehow not-weird

05:33.580 --> 05:37.550
this objectively ridiculous state
of affairs is starting to feel.

05:37.570 --> 05:38.690
And now this.

